# CoreWAF Starter Kit — customer configuration
#
# Copy this file to `config.ini` and fill in the provisioning token, or
# run `./scripts/install.sh` for a guided TUI that writes it for you.
#
# Tunnel v2: a single self-locating token carries everything. The kit
# decodes the gateway URL from the token, redeems against /redeem, and
# receives the full provisioning package (tunnel config, mTLS cert,
# zero-trust secret, observability endpoints, namespace, firewall
# allowlist) in one round trip. No more entering URLs by hand.

# === Required ===

# Provisioning token issued by the operator. Self-locating: the
# gateway URL is encoded inside the envelope, so the kit knows where
# to redeem without a separate `gateway_url` field. Single-use;
# tokens issued for one install can't be reused.
#
# Example: v1.eyJleHAiOjE3MDA...K9.MEUCIQ...
provisioning_token=

# === Optional ===

# Free-form comment attached to this instance for diagnostics. Shown
# in the operator GUI alongside the instance — useful for
# "rack 4, slot 7" or "demo for ACME on 2026-04-25" style notes.
instance_comment=
